> Raise your hand if the biggest question of your week is always, "What the heck am I eating for dinner?!" While we can't actually see you, we're right there with you. We've got you covered, and FYI, the answer to that question is pretty delicious. We're serving up succulent pork tenderloin with a side of roasted sweet potatoes, bell pepper, and poblano all tossed in garlicky lime butter. To finish things off, the pork is drizzled with a ridiculously delicious soy-spiked pan sauce. Talk about a dream come true!

== Veggies ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @poblano pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and diced into ½-inch pieces) and @bell pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and diced into ½-inch pieces). Dice @sweet potatoes{2}(diced into ½-inch pieces). Toss veggies on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast sweet potatoes on top rack and peppers on middle rack.

== Prep ==

Meanwhile, zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced, separating whites from greens). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and minced).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @water{2%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of lime juice.

== Pork ==

Pat @pork tenderloin{12%ounce} dry with paper towels; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork; sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a second baking sheet. Roast on middle rack until pork is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, add pork to sheet with peppers.

Remove from oven; let rest at least ~{5%minutes}. Thinly slice crosswise.

== Garlic Lime Butter ==

Place @butter{1%tablespoon} in a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in a pinch each of garlic and lime zest; season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Set aside.

== Sauce ==

While pork rests, wipe out pan used to sear pork; heat over medium-high heat. Add a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon}, scallion whites, and remaining garlic. Cook, stirring, until aromatics are softened and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour in sauce and cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

== Finish ==

Once veggies are done, toss with garlic lime butter; season generously with @salt{generous pinch} and @pepper{generous pinch}.

Divide veggies and pork between plates. Top pork with sauce. Garnish with scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.